article.headline: Arizona St. 56, Southern Cal 52
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. -- Chris Colvin completed a three-point play with 19.4 seconds to play, and Arizona State escaped with a 56-52 victory over Southern California Saturday night in a matchup of two of the bottom three teams in the Pac-12. Jordan Bachynski had 19 points, one shy of his career high, and nine rebounds as the Sun Devils (9-20, 5-12) snapped a four-game losing streak. Freshman Byron Wesley set a career best for the second straight game with 22 points for the Trojans (6-23, 1-15), who lost their seventh in a row. Maurice Jones added 12 points on 4 of 13 shooting for USC. Trent Lockett scored 12 points for Arizona State. Wesley had 18 points in the Trojans' loss at Arizona on Thursday night.
